· An online portfolio or samples of work demonstrating experience creating great user-centered design solutions is a requirement for application<br />
· Excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills<br />
· Experience working in a collaborative team and working directly with developers for implementation of designs<br />
· Ability to work gracefully and have a bias for action in a fast-paced, sometimes ambiguous environment<br />
· Ability to drive the design review cycle and close on design requirements independently<br />
· Fluency in best practices for information architecture and design, as well as strong knowledge of usability principles and techniques<br />
· Familiarity with the technical considerations needed when designing for the consumer devices<br />
· Bachelor’s degree in design, human-computer interaction (HCI), or equivalent professional experience<br />
· Proficiency in a variety of design tools such as Photoshop, Illustrator, Fireworks, and InDesign</p>
